I might be missing something, but what's the benefit of adding a `WantedBy=` on the target service? If someone does a `sudo systemctl start telemetry.service` (as an example), then that service will get started anyways, and this timer will start running and immediately tell the target service to activate (which it already is).

One existing example is https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-buildimage/blob/master/files/build_templates/snmp.timer#L12.

The use case is to trigger the timer start, which after boot, triggers the corresponding service start immidiatelly when a ```WantedBy=``` service is started, e.g. in case of auto restarting.
